{'content': u'\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nMicrosoft Word - Letter ECOSOC President to STI co-charis -REVISED.docx\n\n\n \n\n   \n\n \n  The President \n                    of the \n\n Economic and Social Council        \n         5 April 2016                        \n\n         \n\nExcellency, \n\n \n\nI refer to the General Assembly resolution 70/1 on 2030 Agenda for Sustainable \n\nDevelopment which launched the Technology Facilitation Mechanism in September 2015 and \n\nthe resolution 69/313, on the Addis Ababa Action Agenda which established a Technology \n\nFacilitation Mechanism including a collaborative multi-stakeholder forum on science, \n\ntechnology and innovation for the Sustainable Development Goals (hereafter STI forum).  \n\n \n\nAs requested by the General Assembly resolution 70/1, the President of ECOSOC will \n\nconvene the meetings of the STI forum once a year to discuss science, technology and \n\ninnovation cooperation around thematic areas for the implementation of the Sustainable \n\nDevelopment Goals. The General Assembly also decided that the meetings of the forum will \n\nbe co-chaired by two Member States and will result in a summary of discussions elaborated by \n\nthe two co-Chairs, as an input to the meetings of the high-level political forum. \n\n \n\nIn this regards, I have the honour to inform you that I have decided to appoint H.E. Mr. \n\nMacharia Kamau, Permanent Representative of the Republic of Kenya to the United Nations \n\nand Dr. Vaughan Turekian, the Science and Technology Adviser to the US Secretary of State, \n\nto act as co-chairs for the STI forum. I would like to thank Ambassador Kamau and Dr. \n\nTurekian for accepting this responsibility and trust that you will extend your full cooperation \n\nand support them. \n\n \n\nPlease accept, Excellency, the assurances of my highest consideration. \n\n \n\n                                                                                            \nOh Joon \n\n   President of ECOSOC                   \n\n \n\n \n\n \n\nAll States Members of the United Nations and \n\nStates members of specialized agencies \n\n \n\n \n\n \n\n \n\n \n\n \n\n \n\n \n\nDivision for Sustainable Development, \n\nDepartment of Economic and Social Affairs, United Nations, New York, N.Y. 10017 \n\nTel: (1-212) 963-9652 Fax: (1-212) 963-1267 email: castillos@un.org; perez7@un.org \n\n\n', 'metadata': {u'access_permission:can_modify': u'true', u'access_permission:extract_content': u'true', u'xmpMM:DocumentID': u'uuid:2e030a2d-fe6f-11e5-0000-d57dabc1456c', u'producer': u'PDF Writer - bioPDF / http://www.biopdf.com / FPG / United Nations', u'Author': u'chaudhry.iqbal', u'dc:title': u'Microsoft Word - Letter ECOSOC President to STI co-charis -REVISED.docx', u'meta:save-date': u'2016-04-08T15:46:57Z', u'Last-Modified': u'2016-04-08T15:46:57Z', u'xmp:CreatorTool': u'PDF Writer - bioPDF (10.12.0.2363)', u'dcterms:created': u'2016-04-06T16:21:56Z', u'access_permission:can_print': u'true', u'meta:author': u'chaudhry.iqbal', u'X-Parsed-By': [u'org.apache.tika.parser.DefaultParser', u'org.apache.tika.parser.pdf.PDFParser'], u'access_permission:extract_for_accessibility': u'true', u'access_permission:fill_in_form': u'true', u'pdf:encrypted': u'false', u'creator': u'chaudhry.iqbal', u'dc:format': u'application/pdf; version=1.5', u'access_permission:can_print_degraded': u'true', u'Creation-Date': u'2016-04-06T16:21:56Z', u'access_permission:assemble_document': u'true', u'Last-Save-Date': u'2016-04-08T15:46:57Z', u'X-TIKA:parse_time_millis': u'1077', u'date': u'2016-04-08T15:46:57Z', u'created': u'Wed Apr 06 16:21:56 UTC 2016', u'dc:creator': u'chaudhry.iqbal', u'modified': u'2016-04-08T15:46:57Z', u'meta:creation-date': u'2016-04-06T16:21:56Z', u'access_permission:modify_annotations': u'true', u'pdf:PDFVersion': u'1.5', u'xmpTPg:NPages': u'1', u'title': u'Microsoft Word - Letter ECOSOC President to STI co-charis -REVISED.docx', u'dcte